<br>
You can be a bad warrior with good gear.<br>
<br>
The best warrior has a combination of good knowledge, skills, and equipment.<br>
<br>
Nobody can dictate how you must play the game.  Since you don't want to be in a guild, you likely won't be doing high end encounters with a large group.  If you plan is to simply play in a single group setting, you can get all the gear you would need to play in such a setting with similar style players. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=quirtevans>QuirtEvans</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/03 11:14:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3069.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:</span><hr size=1> Yes, it's possible.  There is something good that is droppable, or MQable, or single groupable, for every slot.  (Even things like the Blade of Carnage and the Sceptre of Destruction, which were selling on my server for 300k and 500k a couple of months ago, are droppable.  And there's a couple of Cloaks of Flame for sale each week.)  You won't be equipped like an endgame character, but if you aren't going on raids you won't be seeing endgame encounters anyway.<br>
<br>
You'll need an awful lot of plat to get well equipped, though.<br>
<br>
As for eating what you kill, it's possible, but some of the stuff can be rare, and the good stuff will often be camped.  Some suggestions .. once you get to a high enough level (mid to high 50s), the moktor stuff in UP is single groupable, and should serve your purposes.  (In particular, the legs are OK, and it's hard to find good reasonably priced stuff for the legs and the chest slots.)  The shissar scaled BP in the Grey is also single groupable, and is a reasonable BP.  There's also a nice neck item that drops in the Grey (clattering bone necklace).  Depending on how strong the group is, you can get a nice haste item if you spend enough time in SG, you can get bracers in VL, there's a decent bracer that's not quite as good that drops in SD and can be done by a warrior and a healer .. there's plenty of stuff out there, but some of it can be rarish drops, and the stuff that sells well is often camped, so you're going to have to spend some time on it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaylonn>Gaylonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 259<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/27/03 2:20:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3069.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://bellsouthpwp.net/R/a/RafaelSmith/axe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> I would definatley say yes.  Its hard but can be done.  Although I am in a pretty good guild, due to RL issues I don't get to raid much or go on boss mob kills.  Pretty much everyth