<br>
Too true.  If you don't have the weaps and the haste items to hold aggro, then you don't hold aggro, no matter how expert you are at mashing that taunt button and chasing the mob around.  If you don't have the AC and HP gear to be an asset to your group, they might as well let a well-equipped SK or pally tank, because at least those classes have spells that will help them hold aggro off the casters.  <br>
<br>
Part of it depends on the group, of course.  A good group can help even a mediocre warrior hold aggro.  A bad group can steal aggro regularly from even the most uber warrior.   <br>
<br>
Warrior is often a tough class to play.  Your job is to hold aggro, but you don't get particularly special skills to enable you to do that job.  If you want to do your job well, you need to be decently equipped, and you need to play with people who understand how to help a warrior maintain aggro.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eqin>eqin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/03 11:00:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3069.topic&index=18>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   tricky</span><hr size=1> Ben,<br>
